	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99383917914944>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=99383917914944>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99383917914944>HE Enchanter?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99383917914944#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 29th 2:26 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=67705><span id=Sage>Kensuke</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>85 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Someone on another board mentioned that HE (High-Elf?) Enchanters can get better prices at certain merchants, i.e., buy for less, sell for more. <br><br>I'm curious as to exactly how this is done, as I'm hurting in the money department. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99390727039888>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=99390727039888>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99390727039888>RE: HE Enchanter?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99390727039888#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Jun 30th 9:21 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=50451><span id=Scholar>riotgirl</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>54 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.17]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Charisma. Pure and simple.<br><br>Learning and adopting the methods of my more knowledgable peers, let us adopt some quantative analysis methods:<br><br>First of all, there are 5 races which can play Enchanters: Dark Elf, Erudite, Gnome, High Elf and Human (you may all stop laughing now at the 'Cows' :P). The primary stat for Enchanters is Int, with Charisma the secondary stat (used as a secondary check for the 'Conjuration' spell line I believe?):<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;         <br>Base Stats:<br><br>           Cha    Int<br><br>Dark Elf   60     99<br>Erudite    70     107<br>Gnome      60     98<br>High Elf   80     92<br>Human      75     75<br><br>Based purely in terms of numbers, High Elves are the most charismatic race and hence, will receive the -best- prices from merchants, right? No analysis would be complete without acknowledging the role that faction plays in prices. My initial faction in Qeynos was 'apprehensive' which negates somewhat my Cha of 103. However, because I am an Enchanter above 8th level (the spell rank when 'Alliance' becomes available) I can simply cast 'Illusion: Human' (4th level spell) to raise my faction to 'indifferent', and then cast 'Alliance' to increase my faction from 'indifferent' to 'Aimable'. Every little copper saved helps :)<br> <br>Note: (1) I've noticed that in my home city of Felwithe, there is -no- price difference between 'indifferent' and 'aimable' factions. (2) Everybody 'hurts' in the money deparment (non-twinked), but as an Enchanter the -only- items which should cost a lot of money are: jewelry material and spells. Aside from food and water, I simply do -not- purchase anything else from vendors. Sure, Charisma -helps- a bundle when selling items such as Lightstones (and extra gold I do believe with 'indifferent' faction?) but there is precious little else that requires you to purchase from vendors. <br><br>Raising your charisma to purchase jewelry components at reduced prices should be motivation enough :)<br><br>riotgirl<br>(13 seasons fledgling Enchanter)<br>Ayonae Ro<br><br>P.s. Cheap +Cha items: Silver Cat's Eye Agate necklace +2 Cha, Electrum Cat's Eye Agate Bracelets +4 Cha, and the Golden Locket +2 ac +3 Cha (found on Nestling Rat in Qeynos Aqueducts).</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>0 Replies</td></tr>
