	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Alright guys, i have played an enchanter for probably and year now.. been playing for 2 .<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; Ok, what i have learned over this last while is that enchanters are an amazing class.. sure at first they are hard to play and at lvl 20 - 24 they are VERY hard to level. If you wish to make it in the life of an enchanter you must learn your character very carefully the first 20 levels that give you an idea on how to play them in later on levels. When you have learned you enchanter you will be fine after that, I have also learned that not everyone will  play the same as you.. some play with chain stunning and some play with buffs... I play with buffs/mez spells all the time, I find that it helps out more... and if people tellyou to do something or set a certion spell try it. My suggestion is though, if you odn't like that way the spell works.. or it just bothers you cause you dont normally use it.. either use it more often or go back to your normal spells you use. <br>     Now at for Jewel craft you should start tthat at an early level. the best time to start it would be around lvl 15 or so.. that way you atleast have some money behind you by then.  But no matter what class you are ( cept evil races )  Go to Felwithe its the BEST place to jewel craft, you learn skill so much faster there because ALL of the different gems are there. Jewel craft is VERY expencive but as you move on and up in levels you will get more money and hence better at jewel craft.  <br>        another trade skill you chould keep at is Research you dont get it untill you hit level 16 but, in later on levels you will use it alot.. and if you can research really good you will be able to make spells and sell them to either players or npcs for soem good cash. I would say read up on how to practice the research skill as best you can befor attempting regular spells. <br>        Now at lvl 1-5 stay in your newbie zone. lvl 6-10 stay in the next zone out or if you can get a GG to East Commons good exp and easy to kill the things there. 11-15 should be in West Comons ( the next zone over )  16-20 i would say you go to South Karana at the Avirk city. 21-25 stay in South Karana still but more north to the Paw Spires. 26-30 you can either stay at the spires or  go inside Paw, but make sure you have a group. 31-35 move on to Rathe Mts. 36-40-45 you can stay in Rathe mts killing Hill giants (HG's) <br>46-50 go to "the Overthere" zone. you can kill on the ledges untill 47 and then move on to skyfire zone untill lvl 50. lvl 51-55 Kanors Castle in Dreadlands. 56-60 Sebilis.  <br><br>      Now with all them places located you should be able to make a level 60 enchanter in now time and have alot of skills to make him/her. and or keep him/her rich. <br><br>                           Be Safe. <br>                                 Yelar Icewind <br>                                   Mith Marr. </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
