	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=50451><span id=Scholar>riotgirl</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>54 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.18]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&lt;nods&gt; Updating ones equipment is the first real headache for any young Enchanter. The -best- method I've found is a two-fold one: (1) using Allakhazam's wonderful database (SQL?) simply click on the 'Equipment' section and choose by slot. Pick a slot e.g. Chest (casters), and then simply -refine- your search by sorting by class i.e enchanter (I also sort by name and class to produce an alphabetical list of that particular slot for my class).<br><br>(2) Read all the posts in this forum, as well as keeping an ear open on auction. <br><br>You will quickly begin to sift through equipment which will appear in various enchanter forums, either WTS/WTB and can then use the method above (equipment database) to produce a thorough search result for a particular item. Often, there will be player comments which are gems of information.<br><br>Young Enchanter Armour:<br><br>Raw Silk armour:<br><br>Expect to pay between 1-1.5pp per AC. I paid 37.5pp for a complete set minus the chest (Sr Apprentice Robe has the extra +1 mana). Young Enchanters will quickly realise the benefit of Raw Silk when you understand the maxim that Enchanters are "tanks in cloth armour". 37.5pp may seem like an awful lot of money for a young enchanter but I can testify and eulogise to the AC benefits that Raw Silk provides.<br><br>This is an area which I am still investigating as my next equipment update will be the Chest slot -- currently sporting a Fuchsia Sr Apprectice Robe (6ac +1mana). <br><br>Note: Erudite version is +2 mana<br><br><br>Time for a little quantative analysis:<br><br>Chest (Casters):<br>&lt;sorted by av. price based on pricing data from Allakhazams. Take with a pinch of salt&gt;<br><br>Sr Apprentice Robe (av. 4pp)<br>Ac 6 +1 mana <br><br>Gossimer Robe (av. 27pp)<br>Ac 8 <br>(I suspect the robe is actually higher in price than the av. -- can anybody confirm? Also, please note what server you are on)<br><br>Flowing Black Robe (av. 125pp)<br>Ac 8 +5 Sta +3 Int<br><br>Green Silk Drape (av. 311pp)<br>Ac 8 +8 Sta +9 Dex +3 Int +15 Poison Resist<br>(Not strictly an Enchanter Robe, but the stats are extremely good for the price -- at least, to these fledgling eyes :) )<br><br>Robe of the Oracle (av. 585pp)<br>Ac 9 +5 Wis +5 Int +25 mana<br>(This robe is a good lesson in price fluctuations: I have seen it being sold for 800pp in EC then 400pp 10 mins later :P)<br><br>Advisor Robe (av. 1037pp)<br>Ac 8 +2 Agi +5 Int +5 Magic Resist<br><br>Crystalline Robes (av. 2093pp)<br>Ac 10 +2 Agi +6 Int +5 Magic Resist<br>(Sartorial wear to impress the fashion incogscenti -- now with additional accessories such as the Louis Vuitton bag, sweedie. Mwah! :P)<br><br>Blackened Crystalline Robe (av. 4327pp)<br>Ac 8 +6 Int +5 Cha +10 Cold Resist<br>(Hrm, the pricing data is a little suspect. One anomalous player price 10k has skewered the average)<br><br>Shining Metallic Robe (av. 5857pp)<br>Ac 10 +9 Int +8 Fire Resist +8 Cold Resist<br>(Is this the robe of choice when duelling Wizards?)<br><br>At this point, I suspect high level chest slot items are strictly trade only, because platinum is next to useless at higher levels i.e. people are strictly interested in traded items. Also, 5kpp is above the low-mid Equipment range.<br><br>There may well be some factual anomalies and/or omitted details which may need to be rectified by other posters. <br><br>Note: Always bear in mind that the prices illustrated are merely an average derived from player price data, and thus may well be skewered. From this analysis, I have also noted that the price range between a Green Silk Drape to the Advisor Robes can be a couple of 100pp. <br><br>The price that you may pay for a Robe of the Oracle could well buy you an Advisor robe due to price fluctuation. My advice would be to choose a robe and then aim for the low price range. I personally have a Crystalline Robe on my most desirable list, although the Blackened Crystalline Robe is an Enchanter robe by virtue of the +cha. Due to the price of both the Crystalline and Blackened version, I shall have to decide between an intermediary robe: Green Silk Drape, Robe of the Oracle or Advisory Robe.<br><br>Green Silk has nice stats, and has a nice poison resist which would come in handy hunting Giant Spiders or Snakes or Necromancers (:P) but is -not- strictly an Enchanter robe. So it is a toss up between the Robe of the Oracle and the Advisory. For me it's a no brainer: the Robe of the Oracle has that -extra- 1 ac, and the +wis should help reduce jewelry failure rates &lt;crosses fingers&gt;. <br><br>Dearie Me. Verant really nerfed the Robe by making it such a disgusting outfit to wear. It is truely garish and horrid :( There is a conflict within my soul, the very core of my being, as to whether I could be -seen- in such an outfit. Sporting the Robe would forever cease any future fashion show freebies from Anna Wintour. AND it clashes with a Louis Vuitton handbag. <br><br>&lt;hrmpf&gt;<br>riotgirl<br>(13 seasons fledgling Enchanter)<br>Ayonae Ro server<br><br><br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
