	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=99237386085414>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99237386085414>Sense Heading Training Macro</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99237386085414#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 3:24 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=634><span id=Scholar>Altizar</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>104 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.60]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Getting tired of hitting that sense heading button every time it comes up so that you can tell where you're going, use this macro and save a little bit of frustration.<br><br>Assign Sense Heading to Ability Slot 1<br><br>Create a Social Macro called "Sense"<br><br>/doability 1<br>/pause 16<br>/doability 1<br>/pause 16<br>/doability 1<br><br>This will perform 3 sense headings, 1 right after the other.<br><br>Word of Warning : Don't try to type while the macro is running, because it will erase whatever is on the line when the ability triggers after the pause.&nbsp;&nbsp;And /pause 16 doability 1 doesn't seem to trigger the skill.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
